'''Ōtomo no Inagimi''' (大伴 稲公), also known as '''Inakimi''' (稲君), was a {{ill|noble|ja|貴族|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He was the son of {{ill|Ōtomo no Yasumaro|ja|大伴安麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and served as Governor of {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. His court Rank was {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Career == In 730 CE ({{ill|Tenpyō 2|ja|天平|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), Inagimi traveled to {{ill|Dazaifu|ja|大宰府|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to visit his ailing elder brother, {{ill|Ōtomo no Tabito|ja|大伴旅人|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, accompanied by {{ill|Ōtomo no Komaro|ja|大伴古麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. At the time, he held the position of Assistant in the {{ill|Hyōgoryō|ja|兵庫寮|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Right Assistant of the Armory).<ref name="m1">{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=4}}</ref>
Later, he served as a {{ill|Wemondo|ja|衛門府|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Captain ({{ill|Emon no Taifu|ja|衛門大尉|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) and composed a waka about {{ill|Mikasa Mountain|ja|三笠山|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which inspired a response poem from {{ill|Ōtomo no Yakamochi|ja|大伴家持|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="m2">{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=8}}</ref>
In 741 CE ({{ill|Tenpyō 13|ja|天平|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he was appointed Governor of {{ill|Inaba Province|ja|Inaba Province|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, at which time he held the Rank of {{ill|Jugo-i no Ge|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He was promoted several times in subsequent years, including: - {{ill|Jugo-i no Jō|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in 743 CE. - {{ill|Shogo-i no Ge|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in 749 CE, when he also became Assistant Minister of the {{ill|Hyōbu-shō|ja|兵部省|1=Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of War|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. - Governor of {{ill|Kazusa Province|ja|上総国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in 754 CE.
In 757 CE, Inagimi was promoted to {{ill|Shogo-i no Jō|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in May. Following the suppression of the {{ill|Tachibana no Naramaro Rebellion|ja|橘奈良麻呂の乱|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in August of the same year, he was further elevated to {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} for his contributions.
In 758 CE, while serving as Governor of Yamato Province, Inagimi reported the discovery of a set of 16 characters carved into the roots of a wisteria tree at {{ill|Miwa Mountain|ja|三輪山|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Shikijō District|ja|城下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. These characters were interpreted as a divine affirmation of {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro|ja|藤原仲麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s governance.<ref>{{Cite Shoku Nihongi|date=Tenpyō Hōji 2, 27th day of the 2nd month}}</ref>
== Career Timeline == * Date unknown: Appointed {{ill|Shorokui|ja|正六位上|1=Senior Sixth Rank|lt=Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * 730 CE (Tenpyō 2): Assistant in the {{ill|Hyōgoryō|ja|兵庫寮|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Right Assistant of the Armory).<ref name="m1" /> * Date unknown: Captain of the {{ill|Wemondo|ja|衛門府|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="m2" /> * Date unknown: Promoted to {{ill|Jugo-i no Ge|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * 741 CE (Tenpyō 13): Appointed Governor of {{ill|Inaba Province|ja|Inaba Province|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * 743 CE (Tenpyō 15): Promoted to {{ill|Jugo-i no Jō|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * 749 CE (Tenpyō 21): Promoted to {{ill|Shogo-i no Ge|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}; appointed Assistant Minister of the {{ill|Hyōbu-shō|ja|兵部省|1=Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of War|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * 754 CE (Tenpyō Shōhō 6): Appointed Governor of {{ill|Kazusa Province|ja|上総国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * 757 CE (Tenpyō Shōhō 9): Promoted to {{ill|Shogo-i no Jō|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in May; promoted to {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in August for his role in suppressing the {{ill|Tachibana no Naramaro Rebellion|ja|橘奈良麻呂の乱|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * 758 CE (Tenpyō Hōji 2): Serving as Governor of {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Lineage == * Father: {{ill|Ōtomo no Yasumaro|ja|大伴安麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * Mother: {{ill|Ishikawa no Uchi no Mikoto|ja|石川内命婦|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
