'''Ōtomo no Inagimi''' (大伴 稲公), also known as '''Inakimi''' (稲君), was a {{ill|noble|ja|貴族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/noble|qq=}} of the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara period|qq=}}. He was the son of {{ill|Ōtomo no Yasumaro|ja|大伴安麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo no Yasumaro|qq=}} and served as Governor of {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|大和国|qq=Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Province|qq=}}. His court Rank was {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jushi-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}}.
== Career == In 730 CE ({{ill|Tenpyō 2|ja|天平|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpyō 2|qq=}}), Inagimi traveled to {{ill|Dazaifu|ja|大宰府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dazaifu|qq=}} to visit his ailing elder brother, {{ill|Ōtomo no Tabito|ja|大伴旅人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo no Tabito|qq=}}, accompanied by {{ill|Ōtomo no Komaro|ja|大伴古麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo no Komaro|qq=}}. At the time, he held the position of Assistant in the {{ill|Hyōgoryō|ja|兵庫寮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgoryō|qq=}} (Right Assistant of the Armory).<ref name="m1">{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=4}}</ref>
Later, he served as a {{ill|Wemondo|ja|衛門府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wemondo|qq=}} Captain ({{ill|Emon no Taifu|ja|衛門大尉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emon no Taifu|qq=}}) and composed a waka about {{ill|Mikasa Mountain|ja|三笠山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikasa Mountain|qq=}}, which inspired a response poem from {{ill|Ōtomo no Yakamochi|ja|大伴家持|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo no Yakamochi|qq=}}.<ref name="m2">{{Cite Man'yōshū|volume=8}}</ref>
In 741 CE ({{ill|Tenpyō 13|ja|天平|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpyō 13|qq=}}), he was appointed Governor of {{ill|Inaba Province|ja|Inaba Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inaba Province|qq=}}, at which time he held the Rank of {{ill|Jugo-i no Ge|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugo-i no Ge|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}. He was promoted several times in subsequent years, including: - {{ill|Jugo-i no Jō|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugo-i no Jō|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in 743 CE. - {{ill|Shogo-i no Ge|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogo-i no Ge|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in 749 CE, when he also became Assistant Minister of the {{ill|Hyōbu-shō|ja|兵部省|1=Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of War|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōbu-shō|13=User:Immanuelle/Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|qq=}}. - Governor of {{ill|Kazusa Province|ja|上総国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazusa Province|qq=}} in 754 CE.
In 757 CE, Inagimi was promoted to {{ill|Shogo-i no Jō|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogo-i no Jō|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in May. Following the suppression of the {{ill|Tachibana no Naramaro Rebellion|ja|橘奈良麻呂の乱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tachibana no Naramaro Rebellion|qq=}} in August of the same year, he was further elevated to {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jushi-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}} for his contributions.
In 758 CE, while serving as Governor of Yamato Province, Inagimi reported the discovery of a set of 16 characters carved into the roots of a wisteria tree at {{ill|Miwa Mountain|ja|三輪山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miwa Mountain|qq=}} in {{ill|Shikijō District|ja|城下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikijō District|qq=}}. These characters were interpreted as a divine affirmation of {{ill|Fujiwara no Nakamaro|ja|藤原仲麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara no Nakamaro|qq=}}'s governance.<ref>{{Cite Shoku Nihongi|date=Tenpyō Hōji 2, 27th day of the 2nd month}}</ref>
== Career Timeline == * Date unknown: Appointed {{ill|Shorokui|ja|正六位上|1=Senior Sixth Rank|lt=Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shorokui|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Sixth Rank|qq=}} * 730 CE (Tenpyō 2): Assistant in the {{ill|Hyōgoryō|ja|兵庫寮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōgoryō|qq=}} (Right Assistant of the Armory).<ref name="m1" /> * Date unknown: Captain of the {{ill|Wemondo|ja|衛門府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wemondo|qq=}}.<ref name="m2" /> * Date unknown: Promoted to {{ill|Jugo-i no Ge|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugo-i no Ge|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}. * 741 CE (Tenpyō 13): Appointed Governor of {{ill|Inaba Province|ja|Inaba Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inaba Province|qq=}}. * 743 CE (Tenpyō 15): Promoted to {{ill|Jugo-i no Jō|ja|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugo-i no Jō|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}. * 749 CE (Tenpyō 21): Promoted to {{ill|Shogo-i no Ge|ja|正五位下|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogo-i no Ge|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}}; appointed Assistant Minister of the {{ill|Hyōbu-shō|ja|兵部省|1=Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|lt=Ministry of War|qq= (pre-modern Japan)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōbu-shō|13=User:Immanuelle/Ministry of War (pre-modern Japan)|qq=}}. * 754 CE (Tenpyō Shōhō 6): Appointed Governor of {{ill|Kazusa Province|ja|上総国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazusa Province|qq=}}. * 757 CE (Tenpyō Shōhō 9): Promoted to {{ill|Shogo-i no Jō|ja|正五位上|1=Senior Fifth Rank|lt=Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shogo-i no Jō|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Fifth Rank|qq=}} in May; promoted to {{ill|Jushi-i|ja|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jushi-i|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}} in August for his role in suppressing the {{ill|Tachibana no Naramaro Rebellion|ja|橘奈良麻呂の乱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tachibana no Naramaro Rebellion|qq=}}. * 758 CE (Tenpyō Hōji 2): Serving as Governor of {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|大和国|qq=Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Province|qq=}}.
